---
alwaysApply: true
---

- `apps/web` is a visualization and interaction layer only. It consumes public APIs from
  `@diorama/schema`, `@diorama/core`, and exporters.
- The Zustand store may hold canonical scene state plus UI-only state, but
  command semantics must remain in core.
- UI components must dispatch commands only for persistent edits. Do not mutate
  `scene.nodes`, node transforms, child arrays, or selection directly.
- React Three Fiber objects are render artifacts. They must not become the
  source of truth.
- The viewport must reflect scene graph hierarchy so live canvas transforms
  match JSON/R3F export semantics.
- Store camera, hover, panel, gizmo, clipboard, and other transient UI state
  outside the scenegraph.
- Inspector edits, outliner actions, toolbar actions, and viewport gizmos must
  share the same command path.
